dcterms:description: The American English female dataset contains 36-hours of audio sampled at 24 kHz, with Mel-spectrograms computed from the pre-emphasized speech using short-time Fourier transform (STFT) with a 25 ms frame length and a 10 ms frame shift. The input to Tacotron is phonemes with word boundaries and punctuations.
dcterms:title: American English female dataset (en-US Female)

dcterms:description: The American English male dataset contains 22-hours of audio sampled at 24 kHz, with Mel-spectrograms computed from the pre-emphasized speech using short-time Fourier transform (STFT) with a 25 ms frame length and a 10 ms frame shift. The input to Tacotron is phonemes with word boundaries and punctuations.
dcterms:title: American English male dataset (en-US Male)
